article.headline: UMKC 82, Chicago St 81 (2OT)
article.story: KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- Dee Ayuba made four free throws in the last 1:05 of the second overtime as Missouri-Kansas City beat Chicago State 82-81 Monday night. Ayuba, who scored a game-high 23 points, hit two free throws with 1:05 left to give the Kangaroos (10-12, 7-4 Mid-Continent) an 80-79 lead. He was fouled again with 48 seconds left and again made two. Kevin Jones scored with 44 seconds left to bring Chicago State (4-17, 3-7) within 82-81. The Cougars trailed 63-49 after Ayuba made a free throw with 4:47 left in regulation. Kourtney Calvin then scored 14 of his 22 points to bring Chicago State back, and David Holston hit a long 3-point shot with 2.5 seconds left to tie the game at 70-70 and force overtime. Holston, who finished with 22, hit a 3-point shot with 59 seconds left to tie the first overtime at 73-73. Dane Brumagin gave UMKC a 78-77 lead with a 3-pointer with 2:41 left in the second overtime. A steal and basket by Royce Parran with 1:38 left gave the Cougars a 79-78 lead, setting up Ayuba's free throws. Kalu Guasco scored 19 points for UMKC and Tim Blackwell had a career-high 10 assists. The Kangaroos played without leading scorer Quinton Day, who was injured.
